						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="italic">Pillar built into the stone kaṭṭe (raised platform) in front of Daṇḍappa Gauḍa's house.</hi></p>						

						<p>Siṅghaṇa—A.D. 1211.</p>						

						<p>This badly damaged and effaced record is dated in <hi rend="bold">Śaka 1133, Prajāpati, Kārtika, Amāvāsyā, Sunday, Saṁkramaṇa,</hi> corresponding to <hi rend="bold">A.D. 1211, November 6 Sunday, f.d.t. ·27.</hi></p>						

						<p>This inscription seems to record a gift (of land) made to the learned <hi rend="italic">mahājanas</hi> of <hi rend="bold">Santheya Kō[rā]vūr,</hi> for the merit of a certain Boṁmarasa.</p>						

						</summary>
